speech.p:
asked the Minister of Town and Country Planning (1) whether, in view of the Central Land Board's decision that the cubic contents of buildings occupying small sites cannot be aggregated for the purpose of assessing the development charge when re-development is contemplated with a single composite building over, the amalgamated sites, he will make an Order that such aggregation will be permitted, since refusal to do so is imposing severe hardship on owners of such sites and is impeding practical schemes of development;

(2) if he will make a regulation to the effect that where a development scheme has received his Department's approval


the aggregation of the cubic content of all the buildings upon the site of such development will be permitted.
